01:09:32,277 --> 01:09:33,545
(exhales):
Yeah.

1282
01:09:34,580 --> 01:09:37,316
-To us.
-Mm.

1283
01:09:37,316 --> 01:09:41,053
♪ When the rain comes down ♪

1284
01:09:41,053 --> 01:09:42,387
♪ The clouds will roll... ♪

1285
01:09:42,387 --> 01:09:44,389
I can't get over you lately.

1286
01:09:44,389 --> 01:09:47,459
♪ Lord, and the wind
will blow ♪

1287
01:09:47,459 --> 01:09:50,262
♪ You are my undertow ♪

1288
01:09:50,262 --> 01:09:52,564
Can I kiss you?

1289
01:09:52,564 --> 01:09:54,600
♪ Caught in a riptide ♪

1290
01:09:54,600 --> 01:09:56,102
(quietly):
Yeah.

1291
01:09:56,102 --> 01:09:58,771
♪ And I am currently ♪

1292
01:09:58,771 --> 01:10:03,342
♪ In love with you ♪

1293
01:10:03,342 --> 01:10:07,180
♪ My love is an ocean ♪

1294
01:10:07,180 --> 01:10:11,050
♪ She glides like a seagull ♪

1295
01:10:11,050 --> 01:10:14,419
♪ She is the potion ♪

1296
01:10:14,419 --> 01:10:16,088
(exhales):
I love you.

1297
01:10:16,088 --> 01:10:19,125
♪ That makes me emotional ♪

1298
01:10:19,125 --> 01:10:21,460
♪ She is a song... ♪

1299
01:10:21,460 --> 01:10:23,428
Why?

1300
01:10:23,428 --> 01:10:24,763
(chuckles)

1301
01:10:24,763 --> 01:10:27,599
What do you mean, why?

1302
01:10:27,599 --> 01:10:33,105
I-I want to know... why.

1303
01:10:33,105 --> 01:10:35,708
Okay.

1304
01:10:35,708 --> 01:10:37,710
"Why?" Let's see.

1305
01:10:39,912 --> 01:10:41,580
"Why?"

1306
01:10:43,549 --> 01:10:45,818
Oh.

1307
01:10:45,818 --> 01:10:48,620
Well, I love your hands.

1308
01:10:48,620 --> 01:10:54,326
And I love your beautiful,
beautiful, hazel eyes.

1309
01:10:54,326 --> 01:10:57,930
And I love your chest.

1310
01:10:57,930 --> 01:11:01,734
And I love how strong you are.

1311
01:11:01,734 --> 01:11:05,571
And I love that you're
going to become a preacher.

1312
01:11:07,240 --> 01:11:08,908
I love how smart you are,

1313
01:11:08,908 --> 01:11:13,445
and how hard you worked to get
the things that you want.

1314
01:11:13,445 --> 01:11:15,815
And I love

1315
01:11:15,815 --> 01:11:20,153
that you're going to be leading
your own church one day,

1316
01:11:20,153 --> 01:11:23,956
Father Jeremiah Davis...

1317
01:11:24,957 --> 01:11:27,193
(grunts)
You're gonna spill my wine.

1318
01:11:30,395 --> 01:11:31,396
What?

1319
01:11:33,432 --> 01:11:35,534
Jeremiah, what's wrong?

1320
01:11:40,639 --> 01:11:41,807
What?

1321
01:11:43,843 --> 01:11:48,047
Why can't anyone see that
Jeremiah Davis is not a saint?

1322
01:11:49,314 --> 01:11:52,118
What are you talking about?

1323
01:11:55,254 --> 01:11:57,290
You are the most honest,

1324
01:11:57,290 --> 01:12:00,960
genuine man
that I have ever met.

1325
01:12:00,960 --> 01:12:03,395
Why do you think
I'm still with you?

1326
01:12:03,395 --> 01:12:05,264
You're pathetic.

1327
01:12:05,264 --> 01:12:07,033
What?

1328
01:12:08,767 --> 01:12:10,335
(panting)
You want to know

1329
01:12:10,335 --> 01:12:14,473
what goes on
in this honest, genuine man?

1330
01:12:15,841 --> 01:12:17,676
I don't want to be a preacher.

1331
01:12:17,676 --> 01:12:19,745
I don't want to marry you.

1332
01:12:19,745 --> 01:12:22,982
And this whole Chicago thing?

1333
01:12:22,982 --> 01:12:24,383
Are you kidding me?

1334
01:12:24,383 --> 01:12:26,919
Thinking you can
make it as a painter.

1335
01:12:26,919 --> 01:12:28,954
Your work sucks.

1336
01:12:28,954 --> 01:12:31,924
You live in a dream world.

1337
01:12:33,959 --> 01:12:36,162
Why are you saying this?

1338
01:12:40,432 --> 01:12:43,135
'Cause I don't love you,
Samantha.

1339
01:12:43,135 --> 01:12:47,006
How many years
do you have to be strung along

1340
01:12:47,006 --> 01:12:49,108
before you get it?

1341
01:12:51,543 --> 01:12:54,613
(crying softly)

1342
01:12:54,613 --> 01:12:56,949
♪ You are my undertow ♪

1343
01:12:56,949 --> 01:12:58,650
Jeremiah.

1344
01:12:58,650 --> 01:13:00,019
♪ Caught in a riptide ♪

1345
01:13:00,019 --> 01:13:02,355
Jeremiah's dead.

1346
01:13:02,355 --> 01:13:05,091
♪ And I am currently ♪

1347
01:13:05,091 --> 01:13:08,527
-(door closes)
-♪ In love with you. ♪

1348
01:13:08,527 --> 01:13:10,096
♪ ♪

1349
01:13:15,968 --> 01:13:18,971
♪ You're falling down... ♪

1350
01:13:22,174 --> 01:13:23,508
(glass shatters)

1351
01:13:29,215 --> 01:13:31,884
DAN:
Jeremiah, calm down.

1352
01:13:31,884 --> 01:13:33,886
Relax, relax.

1353
01:13:39,058 --> 01:13:41,193
Now, is there's something wrong?

1354
01:13:43,229 --> 01:13:45,731
I have a confession to make.

1355
01:13:48,867 --> 01:13:51,536
I'm not the person
you think I am.

1356
01:13:52,504 --> 01:13:54,740
I murdered my brother.

1357
01:13:56,475 --> 01:13:58,477
I sat and I watched

1358
01:13:58,477 --> 01:14:02,481
as he was beaten up
and thrown into a river.

1359
01:14:02,481 --> 01:14:06,118
I could have saved him,
but I didn't...

1360
01:14:06,118 --> 01:14:09,054
I didn't, I didn't do anything.

1361
01:14:10,956 --> 01:14:12,457
I can't be a priest.

1362
01:14:12,457 --> 01:14:15,294
Jeremiah, we've
been through this.

1363
01:14:15,294 --> 01:14:17,496
God has forgiven you.

1364
01:14:17,496 --> 01:14:20,433
He's forgiven you.

1365
01:14:20,433 --> 01:14:21,767
What?

1366
01:14:23,135 --> 01:14:27,006
But it was my fault.

1367
01:14:27,840 --> 01:14:29,342
I am a murderer.

1368
01:14:29,342 --> 01:14:32,678
Son, I've seen you down
on your knees.

1369
01:14:32,678 --> 01:14:36,349
And God has heard you
and he has forgiven you.

1370
01:14:36,349 --> 01:14:38,717
You must accept that
and move on.

1371
01:14:40,753 --> 01:14:42,922
So, that's it?

1372
01:14:42,922 --> 01:14:44,924
I'm just...

1373
01:14:48,361 --> 01:14:50,029
...forgiven?

1374
01:14:53,599 --> 01:14:56,335
Son, look at me.

1375
01:14:58,537 --> 01:15:01,441
God loves you.

1376
01:15:01,441 --> 01:15:03,209
He loves you.

1377
01:15:06,779 --> 01:15:08,781
♪ ♪

1378
01:15:14,887 --> 01:15:16,622
(sighs)

1379
01:15:35,374 --> 01:15:37,376
♪ ♪

1380
01:15:46,352 --> 01:15:48,587
Hey, how are you?

1381
01:15:48,587 --> 01:15:51,424
I'm great. Uh, can I help you?

1382
01:15:51,424 --> 01:15:53,359
Yeah, uh,

1383
01:15:53,359 --> 01:15:55,627
what's the cheapest
thing you got?

1384
01:15:55,627 --> 01:15:58,697
-Potato chips.
-I'll take some.

1385
01:15:58,697 --> 01:15:59,865
Eighty-five.

1386
01:16:04,670 --> 01:16:05,838
(clears throat)

1387
01:16:08,073 --> 01:16:10,543
I got a bunch of ones here.
Can I get a ten?

1388
01:16:10,543 --> 01:16:12,345
Wait, whoa, whoa, whoa.
What, are you kidding?

1389
01:16:12,345 --> 01:16:15,147
-What do you think, I'm stupid?
-(grunts)

1390
01:16:20,252 --> 01:16:22,154
You okay, kid?

1391
01:16:22,154 --> 01:16:24,623
(grunts)

1392
01:16:30,729 --> 01:16:33,765
Hey! Come on, man.

1393
01:16:33,765 --> 01:16:36,235
-What's the matter with you?
-Get off me!

1394
01:16:36,235 --> 01:16:39,539
(groaning)

1395
01:16:39,539 --> 01:16:41,840
(phone ringing)

1396
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:43,342
(answering machine beeps)

1397
01:16:43,342 --> 01:16:44,676
SAM (over machine):
Hi, it's Sam.

1398
01:16:44,676 --> 01:16:48,147
Leave me a message, or else.

1399
01:16:48,147 --> 01:16:51,150
JEREMIAH (over machine):
Sam, are you there?

1400
01:16:51,150 --> 01:16:53,685
(sighs) I wish you were there.

1401
01:16:53,685 --> 01:16:55,521
I'm screwing everything up.

1402
01:16:55,521 --> 01:16:57,656
I just...

1403
01:16:57,656 --> 01:17:00,993
I just wanted
to hear your voice.

1404
01:17:00,993 --> 01:17:03,628
Sam, listen to me. I have to
tell you something impor...

1405
01:17:03,628 --> 01:17:05,297
(answering machine beeps)

1406
01:17:05,297 --> 01:17:08,467
Sam? Sam?

1407
01:17:12,971 --> 01:17:14,973
♪ ♪

1408
01:17:33,859 --> 01:17:35,861
♪ ♪

1409
01:18:07,193 --> 01:18:10,162
Excuse me, could you
hand me that two-inch brush

1410
01:18:10,162 --> 01:18:11,897
over there next to those cans?

1411
01:18:25,645 --> 01:18:27,279
Thank you.

1412
01:18:29,448 --> 01:18:31,884
What do you think of this shade?

1413
01:18:31,884 --> 01:18:34,153
You think Jesus would like it?

1414
01:18:35,655 --> 01:18:37,923
I-I-I don't know.

1415
01:18:37,923 --> 01:18:40,326
Well, it is His house after all.

1416
01:18:44,664 --> 01:18:47,466
You know... (clears throat)
you look like a wise man

1417
01:18:47,466 --> 01:18:51,070
who lost all his frankincense,

1418
01:18:51,070 --> 01:18:54,206
or maybe his myrrh. (laughs)

1419
01:18:54,206 --> 01:18:55,908
You have no idea.

1420
01:18:55,908 --> 01:18:58,277
You know, I knew
this guy from Honduras.

1421
01:18:58,277 --> 01:19:00,279
He used to ride around
on this mule.

1422
01:19:00,279 --> 01:19:03,916
-Do you have $50,000 I can have?
-Whoa, that's a chunk.

1423
01:19:03,916 --> 01:19:07,819
No offense, but if you don't,
I don't think you can help me.

1424
01:19:07,819 --> 01:19:11,490
Money problems,
I know about those.

1425
01:19:11,490 --> 01:19:13,359
It's more than just money.

1426
01:19:13,359 --> 01:19:16,795
This buddy of mine,
he had money problems,

1427
01:19:16,795 --> 01:19:19,665
then he got both
of his legs blown off.

1428
01:19:19,665 --> 01:19:22,101
After that, his money problems
looked pretty good.

1429
01:19:22,101 --> 01:19:24,637
-You don't get it.
-Oh, I bet I do.

1430
01:19:24,637 --> 01:19:26,138
No, no, you don't.

1431
01:19:26,138 --> 01:19:28,441
All right, painter man,
just shut up.

1432
01:19:28,441 --> 01:19:30,443
Last night,

1433
01:19:30,443 --> 01:19:34,813
I almost beat
a total stranger to death,

1434
01:19:34,813 --> 01:19:38,016
and I have no idea why.

1435
01:19:38,016 --> 01:19:41,787
I'm supposed to be
ordained a priest

1436
01:19:41,787 --> 01:19:43,355
in less than a month.

1437
01:19:43,355 --> 01:19:46,825
My brother hates me,
my girlfriend won't marry me

1438
01:19:46,825 --> 01:19:50,095
because she knows
that I am a total fraud,

1439
01:19:50,095 --> 01:19:53,165
and the only way
that I can fix it all

1440
01:19:53,165 --> 01:19:56,168
is to rip off these guys
that I-I don't know

1441
01:19:56,168 --> 01:19:58,170
using money I don't have.

1442
01:20:00,906 --> 01:20:03,909
Could you hand me
that round brush?

1443
01:20:10,583 --> 01:20:13,419
All right, I'll get it myself.

1444
01:20:18,824 --> 01:20:20,292
(sighs)

1445
01:20:28,167 --> 01:20:29,769
You know what I think?

1446
01:20:31,303 --> 01:20:34,173
I think you should just...

1447
01:20:36,074 --> 01:20:38,977
-...give up.
-What?

1448
01:20:38,977 --> 01:20:40,412
Give up.

1449
01:20:40,412 --> 01:20:43,215
You can't handle this
whole thing by yourself.

1450
01:20:45,551 --> 01:20:47,520
But I know someone who can.

1451
01:20:49,522 --> 01:20:51,256
You know what that's all about?

1452
01:20:51,256 --> 01:20:53,925
You know why He did that?

1453
01:20:53,925 --> 01:20:57,596
He did that so we could
all be forgiven.

1454
01:20:57,596 --> 01:20:59,331
I told you,
I'm about to be ordained.

1455
01:20:59,331 --> 01:21:00,666
I know all of this.

1456
01:21:00,666 --> 01:21:03,703
Ain't enough to know it.
You got to accept it.

1457
01:21:03,703 --> 01:21:06,739
-I have.
-No, you haven't.

1458
01:21:06,739 --> 01:21:09,508
Accepting it means
letting go of those things

1459
01:21:09,508 --> 01:21:13,178
for which you need forgiveness.

1460
01:21:13,178 --> 01:21:16,982
You're carrying all those
things around with you still.

1461
01:21:16,982 --> 01:21:19,051
You got your brother,
you got your girlfriend,

1462
01:21:19,051 --> 01:21:22,254
you got your money,
you're a phony,

1463
01:21:22,254 --> 01:21:25,357
and you're feeling
pretty bad about all that.

1464
01:21:25,357 --> 01:21:28,694
No, son, you are carrying
a lot of baggage.

1465
01:21:28,694 --> 01:21:31,897
Well, I can't just
ignore my problems.

1466
01:21:31,897 --> 01:21:35,468
Well, you can't just ignore God

1467
01:21:35,468 --> 01:21:37,470
until you get things
all fixed up.

1468
01:21:37,470 --> 01:21:39,037
He don't want that.

1469
01:21:39,037 --> 01:21:42,408
You see, the great thing
about God,

1470
01:21:42,408 --> 01:21:44,877
unlike my ex-wife,

1471
01:21:44,877 --> 01:21:49,047
you don't have to be perfect
for Him to accept you.

1472
01:21:49,047 --> 01:21:52,551
And that's when Jesus
comes into the equation.

1473
01:21:52,551 --> 01:21:55,621
Listen, you are standing

1474
01:21:55,621 --> 01:22:00,292
on the doorstep
of the Hotel Forgiveness,

1475
01:22:00,292 --> 01:22:03,262
but they don't allow
baggage inside.

1476
01:22:03,262 --> 01:22:06,699
You got to leave that with
the doorman-- that's Jesus--

1477
01:22:06,699 --> 01:22:08,434
and He's happy to take 'em.

1478
01:22:11,604 --> 01:22:14,273
Well, thanks,

1479
01:22:14,273 --> 01:22:16,275
but I got to go.

1480
01:22:19,812 --> 01:22:23,449
You let go of those bags,
you hear?

1481
01:22:23,449 --> 01:22:25,384
Let 'em go.

1482
01:22:27,419 --> 01:22:29,421
Let 'em go.

1483
01:22:29,421 --> 01:22:31,457
(door closes)

1484
01:22:31,457 --> 01:22:33,459
♪ ♪

1485
01:22:57,049 --> 01:22:59,051
Tex!

1486
01:23:06,625 --> 01:23:08,160
(tires screech)

1487
01:23:11,831 --> 01:23:16,101
Where's my money?
Where's my money?!

1488
01:23:16,101 --> 01:23:18,537
Tex, I need that money.

1489
01:23:30,416 --> 01:23:32,418
What's this?

1490
01:23:41,026 --> 01:23:42,561
Hello?

1491
01:23:45,431 --> 01:23:47,800
When'd you take up smoking?

1492
01:23:47,800 --> 01:23:49,535
I don't smoke.

1493
01:23:49,535 --> 01:23:53,071
-How about the tattoo?
-So what? I got a tattoo.

1494
01:23:54,874 --> 01:23:56,709
Guess where I found these?

1495
01:23:56,709 --> 01:24:00,947
In your key bowl, the first
place Jeremiah would've looked.

1496
01:24:00,947 --> 01:24:02,581
So what are you getting at?

1497
01:24:02,581 --> 01:24:04,817
Remember when we went
to Holland two summers ago?

1498
01:24:04,817 --> 01:24:06,652
-Sure.
-No.

1499
01:24:06,652 --> 01:24:08,888
-We've never been to Holland.
-(sighs)

1500
01:24:08,888 --> 01:24:11,023
I did some research, John.

1501
01:24:11,023 --> 01:24:14,126
They dredged that river,
but they never found your body.

1502
01:24:14,126 --> 01:24:17,630
-Hands behind your head.
-All right, all right, you win.

1503
01:24:17,630 --> 01:24:19,164
What'd you do
with Jeremiah, huh?

1504
01:24:19,164 --> 01:24:20,599
I didn't do anything with him.

1505
01:24:20,599 --> 01:24:23,036
(grunting)

1506
01:24:23,036 --> 01:24:26,639
-Your turn. On your knees.
-(grunts)

1507
01:24:26,639 --> 01:24:30,043
-Where's your backup?
-My right boot.

1508
01:24:34,246 --> 01:24:36,716
-Where's my money?
-Where's Jeremiah?

1509
01:24:36,716 --> 01:24:39,852
-Where's my money?!
-I gave it back. It's gone.

1510
01:24:42,154 --> 01:24:43,489
You gave it back?

1511
01:24:43,489 --> 01:24:46,124
John, the best decision
you can make right now

1512
01:24:46,124 --> 01:24:48,995
is to put the gun down
and tell me where Jeremiah is.

1513
01:24:48,995 --> 01:24:50,763
-Shut up.
-What's wrong with you?

1514
01:24:50,763 --> 01:24:52,631
He's your brother, man.
You've got to help him.

1515
01:24:52,631 --> 01:24:54,299
Why? He wouldn't help me.

1516
01:24:54,299 --> 01:24:56,402
You're wrong.
You don't know Jeremiah.

1517
01:24:56,402 --> 01:24:59,772
You're his best friend
and you never even heard of me.

1518
01:24:59,772 --> 01:25:01,273
He's no brother.

1519
01:25:01,273 --> 01:25:04,744
John, you really should think
about what you're doing.

1520
01:25:04,744 --> 01:25:07,312
Shut up! Shut up!

1521
01:25:07,312 --> 01:25:10,215
-Lord, please be with John.
-Tex.

1522
01:25:10,215 --> 01:25:11,617
Guide his hand and...

1523
01:25:11,617 --> 01:25:12,785
-(gun cocks)
-Tex.

1524
01:25:12,785 --> 01:25:14,119
...don't let him
make this mistake.

1525
01:25:14,119 --> 01:25:16,188
-I'm warning you.
-Calm his heart.

1526
01:25:16,188 --> 01:25:17,523
Tex!

1527
01:25:17,523 --> 01:25:19,825
And let him know this minute,
Lord, that You love him.

1528
01:25:19,825 --> 01:25:20,993
(echoing):
Shut up!

1529
01:25:25,564 --> 01:25:27,566
(phone ringing)

1530
01:25:29,201 --> 01:25:31,070
Yeah?!

1531
01:25:31,070 --> 01:25:32,772
Yes, Mr. Somonoff.

1532
01:25:32,772 --> 01:25:35,108
No, everything's good.
Right on schedule.

1533
01:25:35,108 --> 01:25:37,276
-No problem.
-My El Camino, man.

1534
01:25:37,276 --> 01:25:40,345
-You want it tomorrow?
-That car was a classic.

1535
01:25:40,345 --> 01:25:44,516
Don't worry.
But we agreed on 20%.

